runs.comm: length delivery on the leg stump, he leans forward and defends
further outside leg stump, he blocks on the front foot again
shorter on the stumps, he makes room to cut this time but gets an edge back to the bowler
cuts again, and cuts just in time to get the ball past cover point for one
length delivery outside off, Nawroz leans forward and defends on the off side
outside off again, he wants to sweep this time and misses, but is struck on the leg outside off
length delivery angling in towards the stumps, he goes on the back foot and tucks it towards backward square leg
slightly fuller with some movement, driven down to mid-on and a fumble there gives them two
full on middle stump now, flicked in the air and towards deep square leg for one
knocks the stumps over! The seam movement does it as Bukhari pitched it on good length just around off, Shahzad drove down the ground but the ball nipped in and found the gap between bat and pad
nice movement in again from off stump, Asghar flicks it with the wrists dangerously towards deep square leg
moves towards off stump and closes the bat towards the leg side with a drive for the full delivery and sends it to deep square leg
full around off and it's punched down to mid-off for one
good-length delivery outside off, he reaches out and drive it a bit late towards third man for one
doesn't give him any room and appeals for lbw after trapping him with a full delivery in front of leg but it was going down
full again, just outside off now and it's driven down to mid-off
back of length and angling into the batsman, bit awkward but he tucks it to square leg for one
nips it in from back of length again, he goes back and defends it on the off side
charges down, Bukhari pitches it short, Stanikzai misses and gets a leg bye off his right hip
nips the ball in towards the batsman, but Mangal uses the angle and the pace to guide it just past short fine leg with a well-timed shot for four
fuller outside off now, driven past cover point and point and they do well to come back for the second
full and on the stumps, driven down handsomely to long-on, for one this time

one more for Bukhari! Beautiful offcutter into Stanikzai who was stuck on the back foot to turn the ball to leg, but the ball deceived him and hit him in front of middle and leg just above the knee roll
beauty! This one was outside off on length, just about held its line as Shenwari drove on the off side but missed it by a whisker
bit too full on the off stump, driven straight down to mid-off
slower delivery, Mangal plays early, trying to swipe it to leg but is foxed and the ball goes past him outside off
quicker and outside off, he defends it to cover this time, with a thick edge
too short, bit too wide outside off and he plays the upper cut to send it flying wide of third man for four
high and handsome, what a shot! He came down confidently this time and drove it straight over the bowler's head for a six
angling in towards middle and leg from length, tucked with the angle to deep square leg for two
right in the block hole on off stump, it's blocked back
pushes the incoming delivery towards mid-on with an edge and scampers down for a quick single
good-length offcutter around off, Nawroz makes room and only finds cover point
slightly slower on the off stump, pushed down to mid-on and the ball deflects off the diving fielder's left hand for one
pretty full and coming in, clipped to mid on
back of length outside off now, cuts it late to the right of short third man for one
full on the middle stump, pushed down to long-on
wider outside off now, driven through the covers for one
towards middle and leg, and it's swept to fine leg for one
flighted and full on leg, driven nicely between long on and deep midwicket for one
gone, Nawroz is lbw! Nice flight on the middle stump, Nawroz looks to play across the line and is struck right in front of the stumps
fullish on leg stump, flicked to the leg side for one
slower and on the off stump, defends it carefully to leg
wider outside off, he waits for it to turn and cuts to point
doesn't turn as much from outside off, Nabi looks to slog it to the leg side and misses
keeps a bit low outside off as Nabi goes back to tuck it towards midwicket and vander Merwe's throw doesn't hit the stumps at bowler's end
goes the other way from outside off, and he cuts it to deep point for one
flighted around off stump, clipped on the leg side for an easy single
clears the boundary inside out! He came down, didn't get to the ball properly but got enough to send the ball flying over the covers for a six
pushes and misses as he goes on the back foot to push it through the off side, but it spun and bounced to beat him
leans forward and defends the ball on off now
risky sweep as the ball pitches on middle stump, but Nabi sweeps it to short fine leg
slightly slower on middle and leg, pushed to midwicket for one
slow delivery well outside off, he cuts it straight to point
fuller on the stumps, it's whipped down to long-on for one
slightly flatter and angling towards off stump, pushed back to the bowler who stops with a dive
just over long off! Comes down the track and lofts the ball down the ground, long-off was deep but not right at the boundary and the ball goes over him
charges down again and doesn't middle it this time, finds long on for one
short and just outside off, he goes back to tuck it to leg but can't
back of length towards the hips, he tucks it towards square leg for one
makes a lot of room, then goes back to the stumps and only manages to get an inside edge back towards the bowler, he wants one but is sent back and makes it just in time as Malik gets a direct hit
full and well outside off, it's clipped down to fine leg for one
makes room by exposing the stumps, Malik bowls a slower one and the ball goes between Nabi and the stumps
futile appeal as the ball pitched outside leg, they take a quick single by the time the bowler throws the ball back to non-striker's end
sneaky running again as this ball is clipped to deep square leg and they come back for the second
makes room, the ball is angled in and he swishes at it to send it over point with a thick edge and there's nobody there so it goes for four
makes a bit of room, is hit on the pads outside leg for a leg bye
accurate yorker on the middle stump, manages a bottom edge to the keeper for one down the leg side
slower ball around off stump, he swipes it to the leg side for one
full and on the stumps, clipped down to deep midwicket in the gap for two
slightly slower on the stumps, worked to the leg side again
full on the off stump, drilled down to long-off for one
full again, but on the leg side now and it's deflected down behind square on leg for one
full toss on middle stump, mistimes it down to long on for one
comes down, gets a full toss on leg and it's mistimed down to long on again
length delivery on off, he stays back and swipes it with a cross bat to deep midwicket for one
length delivery coming in again, tucked with soft hands towards midwicket for one
turns the length ball in, he reverse sweeps and finds short third man
goes the other way from back of length around off stump, he doesn't pick it and changes his pull to a slap on the off side
wider outside off, he waits and cuts it to sweeper cover for one
on the stumps now as it turns in, Shenwari watches carefully and defends with soft hands
succeeds with the reverse sweep as it pitches outside off, he gets a top edge bbut it's enough to send it over short third man
soft defence for the length delivery back to the bowler
on middle and leg, from round the wicket, and it's paddled fine on the leg side for two
back of length this time on the leg side, he tucks it with soft hands behind square for two quick runs
full on middle and off, turned to the leg side again
appeal for caught behind as he reverse sweeps, the ball deflects on the off side to the keeper for a diving catch but given not out as it came off the arm
tries the reverse shot again and gets a single this time
wants a quick single after getting the ball off the pad, the bowler gets to the ball on the off side but throws it towards midwicket
came down the track for a swipe and gets an edge past the keeper on the leg side for one
flat one towards the leg side, he pulls it a bit late to deep backward square leg
holes out to long-on! It was a fuller delivery on the stumps and Nabi lofted it straight down to long on for an easy catch
there's something about Zadrans! He comes down the track and launches it for a six with the spin over long on
outside off now and nudges it gently behind square for one
flat and towards off stump, pushed into the covers for one
slower delivery and it's pushed back to the bowler
full on the stumps, flicked straight to midwicket now
back of length from leg stump, it's swatted to deep midwicket for one
full and towards middle and leg, helped with the angle to deep square leg for one
cracker! It wasn't full, it wasn't that short, but he swatted that to the square leg boundary for a flat six!
swishes at it on the off side now, four more! It was fullish, he drove late and opened the face also late to send it over backward point for four
smashed for six! There was a bit of flight for the length delivery on off stump, and it was smacked over wide long on for six!
full on off, drilled down to long-off for one
flighted and full outside off, heaved to deep midwicket for one
third six from Zadran! This was full on the stumps again, right in the zone for Zadran and he launched it straight down the ground for six
full toss on the stumps, turned to the leg side
full again, six again. He can send them flying on the leg side with the turn and does it again for the third six of the over
slow and full outside off, Shenwari waits and goes down on a knee to launch it over the bowler
full toss on off, he pulls and mistimes it to mid off for one
full, quick and wide way outside off for a wide
that's gone high, a fielder is chasing running backwards from short fine leg but doesn't get there. He swiped on the leg side, got a top edge and found three runs on the leg side
short ball on the off side, Shenwari goes for a reverse slap but misses
on the stumps, within his reach and he slogs it to the wide long-on boundary for a one-bounce four!
slower ball outside off, he goes hard at it and finds a leading edge to send the ball high, bowler gets under it easily

two in two, great catch at the boundary by van der Merwe! It was on the stumps, Shenwari heaved on the leg side and it was pretty flat. Van der Merwe waited, took a couple of steps and jumped just at the right time to catch it with both hands at deep midwicket
that goes high but won't be taken! Full on the leg stump, he stayed back and smashed it over the backward square leg boundary for a big six! Lands in the nets
slightly slower on length, he swipes and finds midwicket with an edge. Scampers for a quick single
comfortable catch this time, third wicket of the over. He pitched it up, the batsman heaved on the leg side and only found van der Merwe for an easy catch
too full on the stumps, he dances down and tonks it over the long-on boundary for a clean six! What a way to end the innings. What an eventful last over!
